JOHANNESBURG – South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) spokesperson, Kaizer Kganyago says contingency plans have been put in place to ensure smooth coverage of the ANC conference, despite ongoing protests by employees. Kganyago says the broadcast will not be interrupted, although he could not comment on whether the protests will continue over the weekend. READ: SABC admits workers' strike disrupted programmes SABC workers downed tools on Thursday. They’re unhappy with their employer's current wage offer. Employees are demanding a 10 percent hike, while the broadcaster is offering 4,5 percent. The ANC conference begins in Nasrec, south of Johannesburg, on Saturday. eNCA